Awards

Roman Rivera

1/21/2018

Awards

INTRO/EXPLANATION

Our records indicate that about 699,912 awards were requested between 2005-03-10 and 2017-08-27. After an award is requested, it may be finalized (77.9%), deleted (19.79%), or denied (2.31%). While there are 45 unique award types, the distribution is highly skewed. The 4 most common award types comprise 82.6% of all award requests. While most (94%) of these awards went to identifiable CPD officers, 6% will be discarded as they went to other employees, such as Crossing Guards and Detention Aides. The 496,641 observations of officers with known information (21,409 unique officers), finalized award status, and between 2006 and 2016 (full years of information) will be kept for the remainder of this analysis.

Award Types

The distribution of award types is highly skewed, with Honorable Mention awards comprising 60.23% of the finalized awards to known officers. The top 4 most common awards are Honorable Mention (60.23%), Complimentary Letter (12.41%), Department Commendation (5.07%), and Emblem Of Recognition - Physical Fitness (4.91%). With a total of 299,131 Honorable Mention awards being requested in this data, the average officer in this data has 14 HONORABLE MENTION awards. As displayed by the plots below display, there is a great deal of variation in the number of awards requested each year.

While the variation on Other awards can be largley attributed to the event-specific awards which make up 7.67% of the data and are all assigned at the same time to (almost) all officers such as the 2009 Crime Reduction Award and the Presidential Election Deployment Award 2008, both awarded in 2011, and the Nato Summit Service Award awarded in 2013. However, Complimentary Letter awards, are incredibly inconsistent. While only 15 were requested in 2010, 16,552 were requested in 2011. On the other end, some awards are incredibly rare and prestigious, such as the Lambert Tree Award which is given to one member of the Chicago Police and Fire Department each year for outstanding bravery. Our data only contains 6 of these awards.
